Problem Statement



Heart disease is one of the leading causes of mortality worldwide.
 Early detection and effective analysis of patient health data are essential for reducing risks and improving treatment outcomes. 
 However, large healthcare datasets contain complex information that is difficult to interpret using traditional methods.



This project aims to analyze the Heart Disease UCI dataset using MySQL and Tableau. 
The collected data is stored in a relational database, processed using SQL queries, 
and visualized through interactive dashboards. 
The project helps identify important risk factors such as age, cholesterol level, blood pressure, chest pain type, 
and exercise-induced angina. The final dashboard provides meaningful insights that support healthcare professionals and 
decision-makers in understanding disease patterns and making data-driven decisions.